Also, I just got done watching Primer.  It was a pretty good use of seven grand.

"..And Jesus has been identified as the killer.."

catching up on lost feels more like a chore than a joy.  i'm still 3 or 4 episodes behind and it'll become 4 or 5 tonight.  The only thing that i've gathered from an outside source is that they seem to be important and very good.

I would try to cut out early and catch up tomorrow; but my leave time isn't what it used to be.

and now ray parks jr.
<lj-embed id="5" />

I really enjoyed the movie and I hope marvel continues to make their own movies in the future.  I would like to note a two things.

-Tony Stark developed the MERV?? (see Scorched Earth)

-The movie made me really want Burger King.  We went a local BK location, but were unable to be served do the the immense amount of customers.  How much do you think they paid for that movie spot?

Happy Cinco De Mayo tomorrow.  We're rolling out at lunch.
I have a friend named Olga and Denmark broke her heart so she's running away to Berlin.
It's winter and I cannot find my green hoodie.  Discontent ensues.
I'm building a house.  I'm using a clue board as my floorplan.  Who's up for a dinner party when i'm done?

i'm building a photobooth.  I'm not sure if i'm going for a full cabinet or just the camera/review feature/strip printing.  I need it to be quite fullproof (able to be used when drunk) and functional with the use of minimal buttons.  Someone mentioned the idea of using cheap kodak camera/photo printers in custom boxes, but i'm not sure that it'd be possible to print three photographs 1.5 inch strips with this method.  I'm quite sure i could automate it and use pre-cut strips of photopaper in a standard deskjet; but that'd require a dedicated computer.

cost is another factor; considering construction and consumables.  I would like to be able to operate it at a party for under 20 dollars.  I haven't done much research into it yet, i just would like ideas before i invest too much into a single plan.

My debit card got compromised, but they only got 2 dollars because i have the quickness.  I got to the bank only a few hours before the charges were posted.  My list of suspects involves a number of bars where i started tabs using the card.  It would be all too easy since they have the card on file behind the counter.  The list progresses to online retailers, but i'm less suspicious of them.

I like ichy thump too much for comfort, other than that I believe there is some merit to Cansei de ser sexi.

Today officially has too much driving in it.

I thought the stick sticklee video was the end-all be-all; how wrong was i?

<lj-embed id="2" />

Jackson water taste like it is being pumped from a swamp without any purification.  better yet, they dont know why it taste that way but openly ensure that it's safe to drink.

Last night in a fair stroke of luck, i discovered that my downstairs neighbor and I have a termendous amount of similar hobbies.  I hung out with them last night, which means i didn't watch heroes.  It makes me sad that right as I'm leaving that I find someone that could have been my friend.

Alpha Team is a go for a watery death if caution isn't taken; pictures will be available if we find the northwest passage.  The naked mile will be my next endeavour.
I ate the most dangerous meal in america.

I've been up since 4 am and i have cat scratches all along my side.  Does anyone know about clipping a cat's nails?  I dont want to cut them off completely, but Dexter is getting really bag about using his nails to get attention.  If i clip them so they are less blunt, would it have any negative effects on him?

We're going to see My little pony Live!. I think tickets are either $10 for risers or $20 for floor.

Cats do not like hamburgers.  At all.

The quality of coffee that i purchase for my office has never really mattered to me, but on a whim i got some a little better than folders.  I'm not sure if it's a psychology reaction to knowing that it's more expensive or a change in mood, but i believe it makes me feel less jittery in the mornings.

Dexter is going through a grieving period now that frank is gone which he lets known by constant meow'ing.  I've read that the best way to curve this attention getting behavior is to ignore him when he is doing it and pet him when he gives up.  The problem is that he doesn't give up.  I also believe he might have fleas.

A chemical engineering guy that graduated college with me started working at DEQ today.  I haven't seen him, but I feel assured that he'd show up for his first day.  We make a big deal about those.

Wasbi with jean reno was great, talladega night is not very funny, and i really want to see TMNT.

Sometime this week i'm planning on learning about car wiring.  We are planning to rig nik's ex-roommate's horn to his breaks, so anytime he breaks his car (stoplight/stopsign/etc) he'll look like a giangtic ass who holds the horn down.  It's funnier if you know what he looks like.

I wish everyone's work ended at 3 pm in the afternoon like school was.  I want to go do stuff, but by the time we eat and gather, it's usually too late for most thing.  The alternative to this is everyone start work at 9 am and all establishments stay open to 3 am.

I want to ride in a car for several hours, mainly because I have a book a want to read and the car is the best place for me to read.  Riding in a car really makes me feel a lot calmer.

I could go for some really good BBQ right about now.

Other than that, not much is going on in my head.

Some church had "Weight Watchers will meet at 7 PM at the First Presbyterian Church. Please use large double door at the side entrance." on their billboard according to some chain letter i read.

And it looks like i have to goto train in june.
I'm going to make this into a made-for-tv movie.

-to see the new harry potter book title.


Go to JKRowling.com. Click on the eraser on her desk.

1. Click doorway in mirror to see Christmas tree.
2. Click on the top half of the door to get the wreath.
3. Click on the top of the mirror to get the garland.
4. Click on the spider web right next to the door to make them go away.
5. Click the 4th chime in the window and get the key for the door.
6. Drag key to unlock the door.
7. Door opens to show a desk with a package.
8. Click the bow on the package and it will open.
9. Click the inside of the package and a game of Hangman is shown where you can play a game to guess the name of the seventh book.
10. You can keep playing till you get it right and when you do a check mark will appear.

What's everyone hoping for this christmas?

Having multiple personalities disorder (dissociative identity) is far from a superpower..  Please remove the white trash portion of the "heroes", i'm sure you can think of something more creative to fill the space.  Also, dont kill hot girls because you realize that their power is insanely powerful and ruins your plot.  Make her lose her powers instead.  What i want to see right now is all the heroes bested by a mere mortal, i suggest you use the father of the cheerleader.

Also, i should pickup the christmas edition of the punisher.  Ennis doesn't dissappoint, afterall.

I found this while looking for an answer to a question about terminal velocity of free falling fluids. After studying all the viscosity curves and temperature/fluidity curves, it's really interesting to see what how something visually reacts. Thinking back on it, the only thing i can remember being told about the physical appearance of a non-newtonian fluid is that it's corn-starch or ketchup. Anyone want to finance a kiddy pool full of a cornstrach solution in the name of science for me? On another note, Half of the world makes less than $850(us)/year.
